1
00:00:35,201 --> 00:00:36,286
Get in the car!

2
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:24,626
Hwang Jeong-tae,

3
00:01:25,585 --> 00:01:27,170
do you not want to eat?

4
00:01:28,505 --> 00:01:29,547
Pardon?

5
00:01:30,423 --> 00:01:31,633
It's not that.

6
00:01:33,343 --> 00:01:34,928
Why? He's eating.

7
00:01:35,011 --> 00:01:36,930
It's because he just woke up.

8
00:01:38,139 --> 00:01:41,559
It's all because he's never had to starve
and gets a nice meal three times a day.

9
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:44,145
If we only give him water for a few days,

10
00:01:44,729 --> 00:01:46,940
he'll never pick at his food again.

11
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:54,614
Mr. Hwang, what brings you by so early?

12
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:58,368
I found a book Jin-a should read.

13
00:01:58,451 --> 00:02:00,954
-Here.
-My gosh, this is precious.

14
00:02:01,037 --> 00:02:03,039
THE PRINCIPLES OF MATHEMATICS

15
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:05,792
Can she read this though?

16
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,210
Yes, of course.

17
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:11,339
She's improving by the day.

18
00:02:11,422 --> 00:02:14,008
-My gosh, thank you.
-No problem.

19
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:16,219
My goodness.

20
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:20,557
Jin-a has her midterm exam today,
so she'll come home early.

21
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:22,892
Why don't you eat with me
and wait for her?

22
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,769
Well…

23
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:27,397
Then Myeong-hee should join us too.

24
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:28,898
-Myeong-hee?
-Yes.

25
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:30,191
She's not home at the moment.

26
00:02:31,234 --> 00:02:33,194
I guess her overnight shift
isn't over yet.

27
00:02:33,778 --> 00:02:35,738
-Overnight shift?
-Yes.

28
00:02:36,698 --> 00:02:38,199
She didn't work last night.

29
00:02:39,325 --> 00:02:42,203
She didn't come home last night,
so I assumed she was working.

30
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:44,497
She didn't come home?

31
00:02:44,581 --> 00:02:45,540
No.

32
00:02:46,249 --> 00:02:48,543
Maybe she came home after the curfew began

33
00:02:48,626 --> 00:02:50,837
and left early this morning
before I woke up.

34
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:54,090
After the curfew began?

35
00:02:57,468 --> 00:03:01,264
EMERGENCY ROOM

36
00:03:09,939 --> 00:03:12,025
How can we help you? Are you a guardian?

37
00:03:12,108 --> 00:03:13,484
No, I'm sorry.

38
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:18,114
Hey, In-young.
Can't you tidy up right away…

39
00:03:18,197 --> 00:03:20,491
-Clean this up, will you?
-Yes, ma'am.

40
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:23,494
By the way, I thought you were off today.

41
00:03:24,203 --> 00:03:27,290
Don't get me started.
This is all Myeong-hee's fault.

42
00:03:36,799 --> 00:03:38,760
ETHANOL

43
00:03:39,928 --> 00:03:42,472
I got this. My goodness.

44
00:03:42,555 --> 00:03:43,598
In-young, right?

45
00:03:44,557 --> 00:03:45,642
Do I know you?

46
00:03:45,725 --> 00:03:46,559
Well…

47
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:50,480
Is Ms. Kim Myeong-hee here today?

48
00:03:51,481 --> 00:03:53,858
She didn't come in today
and didn't even call.

49
00:03:54,776 --> 00:03:56,986
She's never even taken a half-day off,

50
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:59,405
but she didn't even call.
I wonder what's going on.

51
00:04:01,532 --> 00:04:02,784
What?

52
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:06,204
What do you mean Myeong-hee is gone?

53
00:04:06,287 --> 00:04:09,040
She's not at home.
She missed work without calling in.

54
00:04:09,123 --> 00:04:10,458
Did you hear from her at all?

55
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:12,710
No, I didn't.

56
00:04:13,711 --> 00:04:16,965
Maybe something urgent came up last night.

57
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:20,718
Then she would've called the hospital.

58
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:23,554
Do you know where she could be?

59
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:25,515
Why are you asking me?

60
00:04:25,598 --> 00:04:27,850
Now, you know more about her than I do.

61
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:31,187
You've known her longer than I have.

62
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,022
You said she's your best friend.

63
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:41,906
Hello?

64
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:43,574
Hello?

65
00:04:51,207 --> 00:04:52,292
Su-chan.

66
00:04:53,042 --> 00:04:55,044
Don't answer Hwang Hui-tae's calls

67
00:04:55,628 --> 00:04:57,255
until things get sorted out.

68
00:04:57,880 --> 00:05:00,383
But if I hang up on him like that…

69
00:05:01,175 --> 00:05:02,510
Don't answer his calls.

70
00:05:13,104 --> 00:05:16,232
Do you want to keep this job or not?

71
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:18,943
-Get your job done properly.
-I'm sorry, sir.

72
00:05:19,027 --> 00:05:21,904
Goodness, what should I do with you?

73
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:24,949
Just do what your predecessors did.
You can't even do that?

74
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:27,910
-I'm sorry, sir.
-Excuse me.

75
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:30,538
I'd like to report a missing person.

76
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:33,124
Is your child missing?

77
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,376
How old?

78
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:38,337
No, it's an adult. She's 26 years old.

79
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:43,217
What's your relationship with her?

80
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:46,179
I'm her boyfriend.

81
00:05:46,888 --> 00:05:48,723
How long has she been missing?

82
00:05:49,223 --> 00:05:50,683
Well…

83
00:05:52,101 --> 00:05:53,519
It's been about 15 hours, I think.

84
00:05:53,603 --> 00:05:55,480
15 hours?

85
00:05:56,355 --> 00:06:00,151
So you saw her last night
but haven't heard from her since.

86
00:06:00,234 --> 00:06:03,112
That's right. We parted ways
in front of her place last night,

87
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:04,822
but I can't reach her.

88
00:06:04,906 --> 00:06:07,617
-Go on. Go.
-No, wait.

89
00:06:08,576 --> 00:06:10,369
Why won't you listen to me?

90
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:13,998
Has it ever occurred to you
that she might be avoiding you?

91
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:16,209
She's not at home,
and she didn't go to work today.

92
00:06:16,292 --> 00:06:18,002
What if she got into an accident
on the way to work--

93
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:23,091
Goodness. People don't go missing
that easily, okay?

94
00:06:23,174 --> 00:06:24,509
-Hey.
-Hello, sir.

95
00:06:25,843 --> 00:06:28,471
And we can't say she's missing
if it's only been 15 hours.

96
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:30,932
It looks like she went somewhere.

97
00:06:31,432 --> 00:06:34,602
Wait. She'd never go anywhere
without telling me.

98
00:06:34,685 --> 00:06:37,355
Come on. How do you know?

99
00:06:37,438 --> 00:06:39,941
How can you be so sure?

100
00:06:40,024 --> 00:06:41,901
Well, for example…

101
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:45,404
Maybe she saw her late grandparents
in her dream and went to visit them.

102
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:49,492
Or maybe she went to see her parents
because one of them collapsed. Who knows?

103
00:06:49,575 --> 00:06:51,035
Hello.

104
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:52,954
You need a haircut, punk.

105
00:06:53,788 --> 00:06:57,750
First, check all the places
where she could be.

106
00:06:57,834 --> 00:07:01,587
Wait another day…
No, come back in three days.

107
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:04,132
Then I'll open a case for you.

108
00:07:05,716 --> 00:07:07,885
I'm already so busy.

109
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:12,557
Where she could be…

110
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:15,560
I need to go to Naju.

111
00:07:16,477 --> 00:07:19,355
It's been a while since I went home.
All I did was call.

112
00:07:23,359 --> 00:07:25,736
Go away! That hurts.

113
00:07:27,613 --> 00:07:29,490
Hey, Digestive Drink!

114
00:07:29,574 --> 00:07:31,742
Your big brother is here.

115
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:33,828
Big brother?

116
00:07:34,579 --> 00:07:36,122
I don't have a brother.

117
00:07:46,841 --> 00:07:48,968
I think they unplugged the phone.

118
00:07:49,051 --> 00:07:50,052
Why?

119
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:53,139
They do it from time to time
because of my grandma.

120
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:55,975
But

121
00:07:56,893 --> 00:07:58,478
is Myeong-hee in Naju now?

122
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:02,273
I wanted to call them and ask,

123
00:08:02,356 --> 00:08:04,025
but you're saying
they unplugged the phone.

124
00:08:04,692 --> 00:08:07,111
Do you know when they'll plug it back in?

125
00:08:07,862 --> 00:08:10,740
That will depend
on my grandma's condition.

126
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:13,743
It could be for half a day? The whole day?

127
00:08:13,826 --> 00:08:15,453
It's different each time.

128
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:23,711
Myeong-su, can you give me the address?

129
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:26,130
190 MAESEONG-RI, SANPO-MYEON, NAJU,
SOUTH JEOLLA PROVINCE

130
00:08:31,302 --> 00:08:32,512
Hold on.

131
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:37,016
Visiting her parents
when it's only been a few hours?

132
00:08:40,061 --> 00:08:41,687
That's creepy.

133
00:08:42,772 --> 00:08:45,775
Okay, I'll just check from afar
and see if she's there.

134
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:50,863
That's creepier.

135
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:56,577
I should pick up some gifts on the way
and properly introduce myself to them.

136
00:08:57,495 --> 00:09:00,998
That will creep them out even more.
Gosh, this is driving me crazy.

137
00:09:01,082 --> 00:09:02,458
Young man.

138
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:04,418
Listen, can you…

139
00:09:04,502 --> 00:09:07,255
Can you call a doctor?

140
00:09:07,338 --> 00:09:08,256
What?

141
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:12,760
My son is about to die right now.

142
00:09:12,843 --> 00:09:15,888
I took him to a local hospital

143
00:09:16,722 --> 00:09:18,808
and they said I need to prepare
to say goodbye.

144
00:09:18,891 --> 00:09:20,851
What's wrong with your son?

145
00:09:21,686 --> 00:09:22,812
My goodness.

146
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:24,772
Are you a doctor?

147
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:28,025
Well, no…

148
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:30,653
I am…

149
00:09:31,904 --> 00:09:35,992
Then why don't I
call an ambulance for you?

150
00:09:40,496 --> 00:09:43,708
Why are you up already?
You should get some more rest.

151
00:09:45,418 --> 00:09:48,546
I'm sick of lying down. It's just a cold.

152
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:51,632
Gosh, you must be fine now,
hearing you say that.

153
00:09:51,716 --> 00:09:54,010
-Drink this.
-Okay.

154
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:01,934
Where's Mom?

155
00:10:02,018 --> 00:10:05,855
She got up in the middle of the night
and stayed by your bedside.

156
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:09,233
She's not in the room.

157
00:10:10,276 --> 00:10:11,819
She was here just a minute ago.

158
00:10:11,902 --> 00:10:13,154
My goodness.

159
00:10:13,237 --> 00:10:14,947
Gosh, I was busy
brewing your herbal tonic.

160
00:10:15,031 --> 00:10:17,366
Wait. I'll go take a look
around the neighborhood.

161
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:19,910
Call the village foreman
and ask him to make an announcement.

162
00:10:19,994 --> 00:10:21,579
Okay. Where's the phone?

163
00:10:24,206 --> 00:10:25,791
I can't believe this.

164
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:27,126
Is anyone home?

165
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:30,421
-Hyeon-cheol.
-Gosh, Mom!

166
00:10:30,504 --> 00:10:32,214
-Mother!
-Goodness.

167
00:10:32,298 --> 00:10:35,676
Where have you been?
You scared me to death.

168
00:10:36,218 --> 00:10:37,303
Where is her son?

169
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:39,513
Yes.

170
00:10:40,222 --> 00:10:42,016
I'm her son.

171
00:10:45,561 --> 00:10:49,774
She said you were my age.
Can you tell me what's troubling you?

172
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:52,818
Sorry?

173
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:57,782
Did she say her son was about to die
and drag you here?

174
00:10:57,865 --> 00:11:01,035
The thing is, my mother
loses her memory from time to time.

175
00:11:01,118 --> 00:11:02,745
I'm sorry about this.

176
00:11:02,828 --> 00:11:04,622
Don't worry about it.

177
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:06,499
I'm glad you're okay.

178
00:11:07,917 --> 00:11:09,001
Then…

179
00:11:09,085 --> 00:11:11,170
-Thank you.
-Have a good day.

180
00:11:11,253 --> 00:11:12,797
Mom, let's go inside.

181
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:15,049
By the way,

182
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:17,885
can you tell me which direction this is?

183
00:11:17,968 --> 00:11:19,720
-It's my first time here.
-Sure.

184
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:22,765
190 MAESEONG-RI, SANPO-MYEON, NAJU,
SOUTH JEOLLA PROVINCE

185
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:40,908
Sorry, we don't have many side dishes.
I should've fried some eggs.

186
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:52,253
I'm sorry you came all the way here
but couldn't meet Myeong-hee.

187
00:11:53,254 --> 00:11:56,340
Seeing you're here on a weekday
instead of at work,

188
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:58,509
I guess you're a college student.

189
00:11:59,468 --> 00:12:02,555
Well, yes… So…

190
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:05,433
I'm about to graduate from college soon.

191
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:09,603
You're the same age as Myeong-hee
but haven't graduated yet?

192
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:12,106
You must've taken a few years off.

193
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:16,694
Actually, I didn't take time off.

194
00:12:18,904 --> 00:12:20,781
It takes six years
to graduate from my department.

195
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:22,324
Six years?

196
00:12:24,618 --> 00:12:28,831
Then does that mean
you're a medical student?

197
00:12:28,914 --> 00:12:30,833
Where? Chonnam National University?

198
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:32,960
Chosun University?

199
00:12:33,043 --> 00:12:34,962
No. It's…

200
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:38,674
Don't tell me
it's Seoul National University?

201
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:42,261
Yes.

202
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:45,556
Cut it out.

203
00:12:48,517 --> 00:12:51,020
Mom, what are you smiling about?

204
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:57,276
So are your parents aware

205
00:12:58,319 --> 00:12:59,862
that you're seeing Myeong-hee?

206
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:03,824
Why are you asking that? How silly of you.

207
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:06,410
Kids these days aren't like us anymore.

208
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:08,120
Don't mind him and eat.

209
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:10,206
Sorry, he keeps interrupting your meal.

210
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:11,415
Go on.

211
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:13,042
-Go on and eat.
-Okay.

212
00:13:14,126 --> 00:13:16,003
Stop talking to him when he's eating.

213
00:13:20,341 --> 00:13:21,884
Thank you so much for today.

214
00:13:21,967 --> 00:13:24,053
I came so abruptly,
but you even cooked for me.

215
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:27,515
Gosh, I'm sorry I couldn't make you
a proper meal.

216
00:13:28,057 --> 00:13:31,685
If you tell me in advance next time,
I'll show you how good a cook I am.

217
00:13:31,769 --> 00:13:33,229
So come with Myeong-hee next time, okay?

218
00:13:35,439 --> 00:13:38,150
Okay. I look forward to seeing you again.

219
00:13:39,235 --> 00:13:41,737
Ma'am, I'll see you next time.

220
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:56,252
We should repair this darn door.

221
00:13:56,335 --> 00:13:57,586
Take care!

222
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:08,013
She's not here either.
Where on earth is she?

223
00:14:12,935 --> 00:14:15,646
No, it'll be okay.
Her mom told me not to worry.

224
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:19,900
She'll be fine. I'm sure she's fine.

225
00:14:24,488 --> 00:14:25,865
Myeong-hee!

226
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:33,998
Where did you go without even telling me?

227
00:14:34,081 --> 00:14:35,499
Do you know how…

228
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:40,254
Do you know what I was thinking?

229
00:14:40,838 --> 00:14:42,715
What brings you here?

230
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:45,634
Do you think I came all the way here
to have fun?

231
00:14:46,468 --> 00:14:49,722
You weren't at home or at work.
So I thought you might've come here.

232
00:14:53,726 --> 00:14:57,563
I know it may creep you out. I know,
but put yourself in my shoes.

233
00:14:57,646 --> 00:15:00,482
-How could I remain calm--
-How did you find out my address?

234
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:04,320
I asked Myeong-su.

235
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:08,407
I know this may creep you out too.

236
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:09,825
I know, but…

237
00:15:16,373 --> 00:15:17,833
Myeong-hee, what's wrong?

238
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:22,880
Is something wrong?

239
00:15:27,259 --> 00:15:28,928
What's wrong, Myeong-hee?

240
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:32,848
You seem like a different person.

241
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:38,228
Myeong-hee.

242
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:00,668
Stay still, you brat.

243
00:16:14,181 --> 00:16:15,975
Who are you, people?

244
00:16:16,684 --> 00:16:18,394
Why are you doing this to me?

245
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:20,896
Well, who do you think we are?

246
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:22,690
Why don't you make a guess?

247
00:16:23,691 --> 00:16:27,194
Is this because of money?
If it is, I'll give you everything I have.

248
00:16:27,277 --> 00:16:30,489
Man, are you treating us
like some petty thieves?

249
00:16:30,572 --> 00:16:33,409
We don't need your money.
Your body will do fine.

250
00:16:34,535 --> 00:16:38,122
I wonder how much we'll get for you.
It's a waste to sell you off to an island.

251
00:16:38,205 --> 00:16:40,207
Hey. Who would buy her?

252
00:16:52,011 --> 00:16:53,846
I did nothing wrong.

253
00:16:54,430 --> 00:16:56,265
Gosh, what a surprise.

254
00:16:57,057 --> 00:16:59,226
You caught on faster than I thought.

255
00:16:59,309 --> 00:17:00,561
Let me go.

256
00:17:01,145 --> 00:17:04,273
I did nothing wrong
to be dragged here like this.

257
