515
00:37:48,808 --> 00:37:50,226
I kept racking my brain,

516
00:37:50,309 --> 00:37:53,145
but I can't figure out
why you're suddenly treating me like this.

517
00:37:54,772 --> 00:37:56,315
I don't want to be by your side.

518
00:37:57,733 --> 00:37:59,151
I hate it.

519
00:37:59,735 --> 00:38:01,988
I don't want to be called a minx
who stole someone's fiance,

520
00:38:02,071 --> 00:38:03,948
and I don't want to hurt those around me.

521
00:38:05,366 --> 00:38:06,701
I can't do this anymore.

522
00:38:13,124 --> 00:38:14,709
Did something happen
between you and Su-ryeon?

523
00:38:16,252 --> 00:38:18,004
Or is it because of Su-chan?

524
00:38:18,838 --> 00:38:19,922
I just…

525
00:38:20,673 --> 00:38:22,425
I just don't want to do this anymore.

526
00:38:26,262 --> 00:38:28,139
There, you heard it. Are we good now?

527
00:38:29,557 --> 00:38:31,600
Do you seriously expect me
to believe that?

528
00:38:32,393 --> 00:38:34,020
You said you wouldn't regret it.

529
00:38:35,521 --> 00:38:37,648
You said we should tell
each other everything.

530
00:38:38,774 --> 00:38:40,943
You said that yourself yesterday.

531
00:38:41,027 --> 00:38:43,487
Then you suddenly disappeared
and had me worried sick.

532
00:38:44,196 --> 00:38:46,449
What is going on?
What are you trying to hide?

533
00:38:47,700 --> 00:38:49,577
Go ask your father.

534
00:38:51,203 --> 00:38:52,371
My father?

535
00:38:52,913 --> 00:38:54,290
I can no longer study abroad

536
00:38:54,957 --> 00:38:56,167
because I dated you.

537
00:38:57,043 --> 00:38:58,794
Why am I running away?

538
00:38:58,878 --> 00:39:00,338
It's because I'm scared.

539
00:39:01,213 --> 00:39:03,841
I don't know what could happen
if I stayed with you.

540
00:39:03,924 --> 00:39:07,053
My life could get a lot worse
than it already is.

541
00:39:08,387 --> 00:39:10,639
I ran away from you because I was scared.

542
00:39:14,769 --> 00:39:16,395
Hui-tae,

543
00:39:17,605 --> 00:39:19,023
I'm scared of you now.

544
00:40:29,385 --> 00:40:30,761
Dad, you're home.

545
00:40:39,019 --> 00:40:40,938
You didn't have to do that, you know.

546
00:40:41,772 --> 00:40:43,816
I heard you met that girl.

547
00:40:45,401 --> 00:40:48,529
It was just a fling.

548
00:40:48,612 --> 00:40:50,656
You didn't have to waste your time
like that.

549
00:40:50,739 --> 00:40:54,452
You told me that men should date a lot
before settling down.

550
00:40:57,955 --> 00:40:59,165
What's your point?

551
00:41:00,332 --> 00:41:02,960
I just wanted to have some fun
before she left the country.

552
00:41:03,043 --> 00:41:05,379
But now that she knows
you disapprove of her,

553
00:41:05,463 --> 00:41:07,131
she thinks this is like the love story
of the century

554
00:41:07,214 --> 00:41:09,300
as if she's in some kind of
tragic love story.

555
00:41:09,383 --> 00:41:10,217
My goodness.

556
00:41:10,968 --> 00:41:13,554
I'm worried she'd cling to me forever.

557
00:41:14,346 --> 00:41:16,140
Just let her leave the country, Dad.

558
00:41:26,442 --> 00:41:30,279
I never thought I'd see you
pull such a dumb trick on me, Hui-tae.

559
00:41:31,614 --> 00:41:33,949
Seeing how desperate you are
makes me think that

560
00:41:34,575 --> 00:41:38,037
I should uproot
the foreseeable problem for good.

561
00:41:39,497 --> 00:41:40,664
Wait.

562
00:41:41,499 --> 00:41:44,001
Please let her leave.

563
00:41:46,003 --> 00:41:49,173
Wouldn't you be relieved
if she left the country?

564
00:41:50,049 --> 00:41:52,968
There are many things
I could do to be relieved.

565
00:41:53,469 --> 00:41:57,389
I insisted that we keep seeing each other.
She kept saying no, but I made her.

566
00:41:58,891 --> 00:42:00,226
She's just…

567
00:42:00,309 --> 00:42:02,853
Her only fault is that
she got involved with me.

568
00:42:02,937 --> 00:42:05,147
You really don't need to do this!

569
00:42:11,070 --> 00:42:12,238
I'll get married.

570
00:42:13,656 --> 00:42:16,617
I'll get married right away
if that's what you want.

571
00:42:24,833 --> 00:42:27,127
Of course, you'll get married as planned.

572
00:42:28,379 --> 00:42:31,840
Did you think you could use it
to strike a deal with me?

573
00:42:41,934 --> 00:42:43,227
Hui-tae.

574
00:42:46,522 --> 00:42:50,484
This is why
you shouldn't kneel down often.

575
00:42:51,443 --> 00:42:52,736
Okay?

576
00:42:53,445 --> 00:42:55,239
It'll look too cheap

577
00:42:56,073 --> 00:42:58,200
when you actually need to do it.

578
00:43:04,582 --> 00:43:06,083
I told you.

579
00:43:08,836 --> 00:43:10,838
The only thing you can block

580
00:43:13,299 --> 00:43:15,634
is this hand, nothing more.

581
00:43:17,011 --> 00:43:18,762
And you're in the palm of my hand.

582
00:43:21,974 --> 00:43:24,018
It's too early to get scared.

583
00:43:24,893 --> 00:43:27,021
I haven't even begun yet.

584
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:35,946
What is it that you want?

585
00:43:37,865 --> 00:43:39,825
I'll do anything you want.

586
00:43:40,576 --> 00:43:44,163
I'll behave myself
and live my life the way you want.

587
00:43:45,164 --> 00:43:47,666
I'll do anything you say, so please…

588
00:43:50,210 --> 00:43:51,712
Please let her…

589
00:43:52,546 --> 00:43:54,923
Please just let her live her life.

590
00:44:03,932 --> 00:44:05,934
Get ready to go to Seoul at once.

591
00:44:06,518 --> 00:44:10,856
And don't come back until I tell you to.

592
00:44:12,232 --> 00:44:14,109
And as for that girl,

593
00:44:15,736 --> 00:44:18,822
I'll decide what to do depending on
how you behave yourself.

594
00:44:37,549 --> 00:44:41,011
What do you mean?
You want to send them to Seoul?

595
00:44:41,095 --> 00:44:44,264
They should get a place to live
near the hospital in Seoul anyway.

596
00:44:45,140 --> 00:44:47,893
Let's have them move there
and get a place first.

597
00:44:47,976 --> 00:44:49,937
The wedding can happen
as we decide on the date.

598
00:44:50,813 --> 00:44:53,482
You talked big
that you'd get everything sorted out.

599
00:44:53,565 --> 00:44:55,818
But were you actually planning
to just push forward with it?

600
00:44:57,820 --> 00:44:58,987
Well,

601
00:44:59,530 --> 00:45:02,616
Hui-tae's woman
issue has been taken care of.

602
00:45:02,699 --> 00:45:04,159
You don't need to worry anymore.

603
00:45:04,243 --> 00:45:07,329
How can I believe you
that it's been taken care of?

604
00:45:09,415 --> 00:45:13,919
Their marriage isn't a business merger.
You can't force it.

605
00:45:15,838 --> 00:45:18,340
Let's take some time
and see how the situation unfolds.

606
00:45:18,424 --> 00:45:19,508
Are you hoping

607
00:45:21,051 --> 00:45:23,887
the wedding will be called off?

608
00:45:27,182 --> 00:45:30,102
We should put the broken pieces
back together for both families' sake.

609
00:45:30,853 --> 00:45:32,479
Those broken pieces

610
00:45:33,355 --> 00:45:35,274
could become weapons.

611
00:45:39,695 --> 00:45:40,946
Is this

612
00:45:41,947 --> 00:45:43,490
a threat?

613
00:45:43,574 --> 00:45:47,870
No, I'm offering you a word of advice
to help you make a wise decision.

614
00:45:59,131 --> 00:46:00,549
Seoul?

615
00:46:01,758 --> 00:46:03,093
So?

616
00:46:03,177 --> 00:46:04,761
I said, no way.

617
00:46:05,429 --> 00:46:07,139
Gosh, I must've been out of my mind.

618
00:46:07,222 --> 00:46:09,892
I practically walked into the tiger's den
to keep warm.

619
00:46:10,684 --> 00:46:13,228
I'm grateful to the girl
he cheated on you with.

620
00:46:13,312 --> 00:46:16,315
At least we had that to protect us
from being eaten up.

621
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:27,576
Don't give him iced water.

622
00:46:28,243 --> 00:46:30,829
Hey, it's just one glass.
Don't make such a fuss.

623
00:46:30,913 --> 00:46:31,997
Dad.

624
00:46:32,623 --> 00:46:33,832
There's something I must tell you.

625
00:46:35,167 --> 00:46:37,503
What is it? Is it about work?

626
00:46:43,717 --> 00:46:46,762
It's something you should know.

627
00:46:52,017 --> 00:46:55,354
Are you saying you planned the whole thing
from the get-go?

628
00:46:57,314 --> 00:46:58,649
You…

629
00:46:58,732 --> 00:47:00,108
Lee Su-ryeon! You little…

630
00:47:00,192 --> 00:47:01,735
Dad, no!

631
00:47:03,695 --> 00:47:05,697
Dad, please.

632
00:47:11,828 --> 00:47:12,829
Forget it.

633
00:47:13,539 --> 00:47:17,000
Talking about who's at fault
will only upset me more.

634
00:47:17,751 --> 00:47:19,545
It may be a blessing in disguise.

635
00:47:20,337 --> 00:47:22,881
The situation has worked out in our favor.

636
00:47:22,965 --> 00:47:23,966
Dad.

637
00:47:24,633 --> 00:47:27,052
We should tell them the truth.

638
00:47:27,844 --> 00:47:29,054
What do you mean?

639
00:47:29,638 --> 00:47:31,640
Are you saying
we should tell Hwang Gi-nam about this?

640
00:47:32,307 --> 00:47:34,142
I told you.

641
00:47:34,226 --> 00:47:37,688
If we don't do anything,
Myeong-hee will be made the scapegoat.

642
00:47:39,356 --> 00:47:41,525
Listen, Su-chan. Myeong-hee…

643
00:47:41,608 --> 00:47:43,193
I know it's unfortunate.

644
00:47:43,277 --> 00:47:47,489
But we must save our family first
and compensate her somehow later.

645
00:47:47,573 --> 00:47:49,992
That's what Su-ryeon was thinking
when she started this.

646
00:47:50,075 --> 00:47:53,120
This all happened to save our family,
so we must make things right.

647
00:47:53,203 --> 00:47:54,663
No, we can never do that.

648
00:47:54,746 --> 00:47:56,498
If we suddenly reveal that,

649
00:47:56,582 --> 00:47:58,917
it's practically throwing our family
at Hwang Gi-nam as prey.

650
00:47:59,001 --> 00:48:00,127
So do you mean

651
00:48:00,210 --> 00:48:03,880
you want to throw Myeong-hee instead
and put an end to this?

652
00:48:03,964 --> 00:48:05,424
What's wrong with that?

653
00:48:05,507 --> 00:48:09,052
-To be frank, she's not even our family.
-Dad!

654
00:48:18,395 --> 00:48:19,813
I'm sorry.

655
00:48:20,480 --> 00:48:23,609
I'm afraid I can't obey you this time.

656
00:48:24,443 --> 00:48:25,569
What?

657
00:48:26,403 --> 00:48:27,946
Hey, Lee Su-chan! You…

658
00:48:31,658 --> 00:48:33,327
Dad!

659
00:48:33,410 --> 00:48:35,579
-Dad.
-Dad!

660
00:48:35,662 --> 00:48:37,497
Open your eyes.

661
00:48:37,581 --> 00:48:39,333
-Dad!
-Dad!

662
00:48:42,753 --> 00:48:44,796
He was lucky this time.

663
00:48:44,880 --> 00:48:46,590
Like I've always told you,

664
00:48:46,673 --> 00:48:49,676
stress is the most deadly disease
for patients with angina.

665
00:48:50,719 --> 00:48:52,638
He may suffer a cardiac infarction,

666
00:48:52,721 --> 00:48:56,016
so you must make sure
he gets absolute rest.

667
00:48:58,101 --> 00:49:00,145
How long has father been like that?

668
00:49:02,272 --> 00:49:04,524
Why didn't you tell me?

669
00:49:07,569 --> 00:49:10,155
If I did, would it have made a difference?

670
00:49:15,619 --> 00:49:17,079
Don't tell

671
00:49:18,497 --> 00:49:19,998
Hwang Gi-nam.

672
00:49:22,959 --> 00:49:25,879
-Lee Su-ryeon. How could you still…
-I will…

673
00:49:27,756 --> 00:49:29,883
I will go to Seoul.

674
00:49:33,011 --> 00:49:34,638
Since I started all of this,

675
00:49:35,472 --> 00:49:37,307
I'll take responsibility.

676
00:49:39,810 --> 00:49:41,228
Both Myeong-hee and Dad

677
00:49:42,104 --> 00:49:43,980
did nothing wrong.

678
00:49:55,909 --> 00:49:57,953
Yes, you made the right choice.

679
00:49:58,870 --> 00:50:01,164
My son has a house in Seoul,

680
00:50:01,248 --> 00:50:03,875
so they can stay there
until they find a new home.

681
00:50:05,001 --> 00:50:06,044
Yes.

682
00:50:06,128 --> 00:50:09,047
Then I'll make the preparations
for them to leave immediately.

683
00:50:10,841 --> 00:50:12,384
Yes, okay.

684
00:51:05,020 --> 00:51:06,271
"It's nothing?"

685
00:51:07,105 --> 00:51:12,068
So I canceled my plans on my day off
and covered for you over nothing?

686
00:51:12,861 --> 00:51:16,114
Hey, are you acting up
since you'll be quitting soon?

687
00:51:17,073 --> 00:51:18,200
No.

688
00:51:19,242 --> 00:51:20,702
Why do you even come to work?

689
00:51:21,286 --> 00:51:23,622
It seems like your heart
is already in Germany.

690
00:51:24,289 --> 00:51:27,042
If you're going to skip work,
just stop coming at all.

691
00:51:28,001 --> 00:51:29,294
I'm sorry.

692
00:51:40,096 --> 00:51:43,266
Are you sure nothing happened yesterday?

693
00:51:45,352 --> 00:51:48,313
I'm sorry. You must've had a tough time.

694
00:51:48,396 --> 00:51:49,481
It's okay.

695
00:51:50,232 --> 00:51:53,610
By the way,
did you talk to Mr. Hwang Hui-tae?

696
00:51:56,655 --> 00:51:59,241
He came to the hospital yesterday
looking for you.

697
00:52:00,450 --> 00:52:02,911
I think I said something
that must've worried him.

698
00:52:03,495 --> 00:52:05,288
He seemed awfully concerned.

699
00:52:11,002 --> 00:52:12,796
HUI-TAE'S SONGWRITING NOTEBOOK

700
00:52:12,879 --> 00:52:14,464
It's a Teacher's Day present.

701
00:52:14,548 --> 00:52:17,008
Write a song that will win
the University Song Festival.

702
00:52:20,554 --> 00:52:22,430
I have a present for you too.

703
00:52:23,014 --> 00:52:24,432
You do?

704
00:52:27,435 --> 00:52:31,273
Here you go.
This is for the upcoming finals.

705
00:52:31,356 --> 00:52:34,568
And these are for next year.

706
00:52:35,569 --> 00:52:36,778
And…

707
00:52:38,238 --> 00:52:40,740
This is a math concept notebook
that I organized myself.

708
00:52:40,824 --> 00:52:42,909
It'll be more useful
than your reference books.

709
00:52:44,536 --> 00:52:48,206
Why are you giving me a book
for next year already?

710
00:52:49,124 --> 00:52:51,084
You can just give it to me next year.

711
00:52:52,168 --> 00:52:54,045
I can't give it to you next year.

712
00:52:56,214 --> 00:52:58,091
Today is our last lesson.

713
00:53:17,861 --> 00:53:19,738
You can just listen from there.

714
00:53:21,907 --> 00:53:23,783
I just came to say goodbye.

715
00:53:28,914 --> 00:53:30,415
I'm going to Seoul tomorrow.

716
00:53:32,417 --> 00:53:33,877
I probably

717
00:53:34,794 --> 00:53:37,505
won't ever be coming back.

718
00:53:42,510 --> 00:53:43,803
Okay.

719
00:53:46,973 --> 00:53:50,018
I wanted to thank you before I left.

720
00:53:56,024 --> 00:53:58,526
The few weeks we spent together

721
00:54:00,403 --> 00:54:02,280
were the happiest moments

722
00:54:04,282 --> 00:54:06,910
in my entire life.

723
00:54:10,956 --> 00:54:12,332
Thank you.

724
00:54:27,889 --> 00:54:31,101
Can I come closer for a moment?

725
00:55:12,976 --> 00:55:14,394
I'm sorry.

726
00:55:15,687 --> 00:55:17,647
I tried my best to be careful,

727
00:55:19,441 --> 00:55:20,984
but I broke it.

728
00:55:25,655 --> 00:55:27,157
That's how I am.

729
00:55:28,742 --> 00:55:30,660
Anything that comes close to me

730
00:55:31,453 --> 00:55:33,371
keeps getting broken.

731
00:55:36,249 --> 00:55:38,293
I hope you continue…

732
00:55:42,338 --> 00:55:45,341
to bravely go down the path

733
00:55:46,384 --> 00:55:48,261
that you wanted to take.

734
00:55:50,722 --> 00:55:52,432
You are

735
00:55:54,350 --> 00:55:57,479
a strong person that no one can break.

736
00:56:05,862 --> 00:56:07,197
You too.

737
00:56:10,033 --> 00:56:11,493
I hope you stay strong

738
00:56:12,911 --> 00:56:14,913
and live bravely.

739
00:56:33,723 --> 00:56:35,683
Look back.

740
00:56:37,644 --> 00:56:39,104
Look back.

741
00:56:40,939 --> 00:56:42,524
Look back.

742
00:56:45,443 --> 00:56:46,653
Look back.

743
00:56:50,657 --> 00:56:52,158
Look back.

744
00:56:55,912 --> 00:56:57,163
Look back…

745
00:57:35,702 --> 00:57:37,454
You'll ruin everything.

746
00:57:39,831 --> 00:57:42,834
Just like your father ruined your life,

747
00:57:43,543 --> 00:57:44,919
you'll end up ruining

748
00:57:45,003 --> 00:57:47,964
Hui-tae's life if you stay next to him.

749
00:57:48,590 --> 00:57:50,508
He's your son.

750
00:57:53,344 --> 00:57:54,554
If you're curious,

751
00:57:55,305 --> 00:57:58,057
stay right next to him and watch

752
00:57:59,476 --> 00:58:00,643
how far

753
00:58:01,561 --> 00:58:03,730
I can go.

754
00:58:06,733 --> 00:58:07,901
Please…

755
00:58:10,153 --> 00:58:11,654
leave Hui-tae alone.

756
00:58:15,533 --> 00:58:17,076
I'll break up with him.

